<p><strong>Job Descriptions</strong> <br /><span style="color: #808080;">Family Entertainment Group's goal is to have a highly trained, professional staff throughout our organization. To REACH this goal, it is necessary to define each person's role within the organization and provide clear guidance on how to succeed in their current position. Posted below are job descriptions for each of the positions that we offer in our field organization. The purpose of the job description is to provide clear objectives for each coworker in terms of job responsibilities and expectations. </span><br /><br /><span style="color: #808080;">Each job description is broken out into sections:</span> <br /><br /><strong>&nbsp;- Qualification - </strong><span style="color: #808080;">The set of skills or training a person should possess in order to succeed in the position.</span> <br /><strong>&nbsp;- General Job Responsibilities - </strong><span style="color: #808080;">Duties that are required by all coworker.</span> <br /><strong>&nbsp;- Specific Job Responsibilities - </strong><span style="color: #808080;">Duties specific to the individual coworker.</span> <br /><strong>&nbsp;- Supervisory Job Responsibilities (if applicable) - </strong><span style="color: #808080; background-color: #ffffff;">Addition duties relating to the management of coworker. </span><br /><br /><span style="color: #808080;">The job descriptions can be modified by the hiring manger to fit the responsibilities of the individual coworker. The posted job descriptions should serve as a guideline in developing a job description however it is the responsibility of the hiring manager to design a job description specific to the individual. Task can be added or removed based on the needs of the location. </span><br /><br /><span style="color: #808080;">The job descriptions are a very important tool for both the coworker and their direct supervisor and will serve as a key evaluation tool during annual reviews. As such, each employee in the organization should have a job description that has been reviewed and signed by the coworker and the manager.</span></p>
